kground_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top background=http://www.cafenet.plus.com/The_Magicians_Tower/Images/Background_1.gif class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izudin@themagicianstower>Izudin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 202<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 3:39:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Soloing in PoP with new spells - possible?</span><hr size=1> Ok we have read over the last weeks that soloing in PoP is not really viable with the old tools. However I have not read any post yet stating how (if) the new spells help with it. Can someone who has gotten the more important spells tell us if they enable soloing again? (like new pets, BO V, Planar Heal, summoned belts and weapons...)<br>
<br>
I can imagine that those who already have a full spell book likely group more than solo, so it will probably take some time until we get reports from the soloers among us. Still would love to hear what effect the new spells really have.<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=omegasyphon>omegasyphon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 610<br> <font color=#333333>(11/17/02 4:18:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   comment</span><hr size=1> well you can solo somewhat. kiting is still an ok tactic but sending in your pet against a mob with just nukes and heals is very limited to about tier one planes. mobs hit really hard and fast in pop <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilmir123>Kilmir123</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.lowlandelites.net/vb/avatar.php?userid=13&dateline=1034772585" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/02 2:19:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: comment</span><hr size=1> Soloing is viable to a certain degree. You can kill mobs, and with canni-pet you do get mana back rather fast. But it's not without danger and 1 good quad of a mob can literally kill your pet from 40%. Plus you kill way slower, mostly because pets don't live long enough to make BO or a DS viable manawise.<br>
<br>
Tier 1 you can do stuff in PoD and PoI pretty well, but need about 8-10 pets per kill and that's with nuking at the end which leaves me at roughly 40% mana from fm at start, with KEI and PotC.<br>
<br>
A lvl 63 mage friend of mine soloed a bit in PoV last night before I asked him into my group. Tonight we're going to try duo with chaining the 61 air pets. I'll give a small report how that went <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p>Arch Mage Rhand Kinslayer<br>
Officer of Lowland Elites<br>
Antonius Bayle<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=39733">Magelo</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rhionsligo>rhionsligo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1218<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/02 2:56:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   I know how it will go...</span><hr size=1> I know how it will go.  Its not bad at all.  Ive done it a few times now, and I'd wager its about 2/3 as good as a full scale balanced exp group in Valor.  Not bad for two people wingin' it by sending pets. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wayfarerman>WayfarerMan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 289<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/02 3:27:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.molinari-dist.com/Wayfarer.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I know how it will go...</span><hr size=1> A 2 mage and necro group in PoV went surprisingly well. We built up a huge pet group after a while (with a shaman in attendance). 3 mages, 2 necros and a shaman is s-i-c-k.<br>
<br>
We definitely proved that you don't NEED an enchanter, tank and cleric to fight in Valor. We seriously cranked through some xp with pets. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27498">www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27498</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
