Whatever is said in Latin sounds profound.<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 470<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/02 4:00:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Solo...</span><hr size=1> I can solo with pure power tactic....<br>
Found nice spot in PoN killing Butterflies, they still Blue at L65 and give good exp solo.<br>
Pull with Malise, run to pet, fire 2 FoT, then chain heal until mob dead, usually leave me at 50-60% mana left depending on resist and if mob get a luck roll.<br>
<br>
Using Epic and more or less forced to use L64 heal with L60 heal combo. Not very effective, but working if you not mind some downtime. (like if there is a good movie on tv) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1405<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/02 5:44:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sebminas.com/eq/baby.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing in PoP with new spells - possible?</span><hr size=1> i got a planarian larve down to 9% just now using ward of xegony, buffed with blades of walnan, belt of magikot, phantom plate, and muzzle of mardu, burnout 5, and cadeau of flame. i was playing pet cleric with the L60 heal. i assume if i gave the pet virtue and other hp/ac buffs it would have made a better tank and probably would have worked. as for enrage, the way to deal with that would be to /pet hold before it happens and just nuke it. im not going to give up till i solo it :P<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=immlazen>Immlazen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#333333>(11/18/02 8:37:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Soloing in PoP with new spells - possible?</span><hr size=1> I like those that are trying to find ways for us to effectively solo.  I however, think we have been slapped in a face when I watch a Enchanter solo nonstop.  Plus the fact that the Enchanter is needed more in a group then a Mage.  They have the best of both worlds. <br>
<br>
NO!  I dont want the Enchanter class to be nerfed.  I want the Magicians class to be made able to solo effectively.  <br>
<br>
Also, Druids/Wiz/Necros...all solo decently within POP.  And they should.  I personnally feel that classes that have harder times getting a group should have it easier when it comes to solo.<br>
<br>
Why are we LFG for 30+ minutes and have no decent way to pass the time by soloing?  VI needs to understand everyone that play EQ do not have 2+ hours to play.  <br>
<br>
Immlazen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etadanikm>EtadanikM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 12:17:18 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing in PoP with new spells - possible?</span><hr size=1> Druids, necros, wizards, etc. do not have a very good time soloing in PoP after a certain point.  Read Zaar's post on eqnecro or FOH board for more information.<br>
<br>
Mages do have it less than the above mentioned classes soloing in PoP, I agree, but I also feel that mages are ultimately BETTER groupers than those classes in PoP.  <br>
You may argue otherwise, but I think it might've been the scheme VI used to balance the classes.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ayasaki>Ayasaki</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 290<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 10:58:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing in PoP with new spells - possible?</span><hr size=1> Well I was soloing in PoD today fighting large size spiders,blue to lvl 65,max hit from 250 to 330.lvl 61 air pet has amazing tank ability I'd say,just rotate Black Steel and Planar Renewal,mount on horse,sometimes click boots if spiders cast a lot so pet isnt losing hp.2% aa per kill,not sure if it's good or bad.Best exp in one single kill I got in from frogs in PoS,but those are extreme tough. I had to log on my friend's cleric to help to kill 1.But,it's 8% aa per kill heh.<br>
<br>
My conclusion is that soloing is indeed doable in the first tier of planes,without add.In tier 2+ mobs hit too hard to solo for mages. <p>Lvl 65 Arch Convoker Ayasaki Wakana</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zeem@themagicianstower>Zeem</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 473<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 12:16:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Frogs...</span><hr size=1> Saw a bard solo a frog in PoS, 14% AA a kill, took about 15mins . so he was working for it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=walk>Walk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 579<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 7:28:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Frogs...</span><hr size=1> Is Solb still blue at 61+?  Like the imps/freeti.  If you can pull those solo... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sirellyn@themagicianstower>Sirellyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 153<br> <font color=#333333>(11/19/02 9:54:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7890.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hard to solo</span><hr size=1> I'm amazed how hard it is to solo.  I pretty much have to make sure I have a good group together to get good XP.<br>
<br>
I can't agree with Jaytee and soloing.  I log on EQ earlier on in the day and next to none of my guild is on.  Check my friends list and either people are already in groups or not enough people to do anything major.  I'm litterally stuck soloing or tradeskilling until later that evening.<br>
<br>
At 64th I'm in dire need of spells.  I've gotten one spectral scroll so far.  Summon jewlery bag.  While neat, it hardly helps soloing at all.  I don't have epic, but I do have the 62nd water pet.  Use burnout V, flameshield of Ro, and don't have any of the summoned weapon spells.  I don't even have the 60th level pet heal, as it's still extremely rare.<br>
<br>
I've tried kiting mobs, even without pet taunt as soon as the mobs turn to the pet and I start to nuke those 5 seconds or so of the mob fighting the pet takes it down a horribly huge chunk.  It's so dangerous it's not even funny.  Not a viable method.<br>
<br>
I don't have the pet heals to even try to keep the pet alive for full on tankage.  It couldn't even stand up to a light blue with that method right now.<br>
<br>
Chain pets are the only way I can effectively solo, and then it's tough and time consuming to take down light blues.  And those that are barely dark blues are a seriously dangerous proposition.<br>
<br>
You know overall I'm really happy with this expansion, and I only do have a few things that strike me.  Right now soloing is big because it's damn hard to get a proper group together in PoP half the time.<br>
<br>
All that said, I would only suggest 2 changes.<br>
<br>
1.) Certain spells for some classes should be made easy to get, but questable.  Actually wizards are the ones most deserving of these.  But mages certainly need a few.  Bolt of talon was nice, but I would have perferred ward of xegony.  Pet upgrades are by far the most important for mages.  We need a way to get our new pet heal easier as well.<br>
<br>
